                                                                  (default, 'datetime', 'A DateTime object in many programming languages describes a date and a time of day. It can express either an instant in time or a position on a calendar, depending on the context in which it is used and the specific implementation. This tag can be used for all date and time related issues.', 0),
                                                                  (default, 'perl', 'Perl is a procedural, high-level, general-purpose, dynamic programming language, known for its native support of regular expressions and string parsing capabilities. Please use this tag for questions about Perl in general. For things related to the new (but related) language Raku (formerly "Perl 6"), please use the raku tag. For Perl-style regular expressions in other languages, use the regex tag, or, if they are based on the PCRE library, the pcre tag.', 0),
